<TITLE> bdnews24.com launches arts and literature site </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 18 (bdnews24.com) -- bdnews24.com, the country's first online newspaper, has unveiled its literature and arts site at a gala event in Dhanmondi. The website was formally inaugurated Thursday at Bengal Shilpalaya in Dhanmondi, at a function attended by some of the country's most celebrated artists. Playwright Saeed Ahmed, writer Hasnat Abdul Hye and columnist Syed Abul Maqsud, together with poets Altaf Hossain and Mohammad Rafiq, professor and critic Azfar Hossain, cartoonist Shishir Bhattacharya, artist Salimullah Khan and a number of academics attended the function. They gave their opinions and recommendations about the new page. The bilingual arts and literature section accessible at http://arts.bdnews24.com features original prose and poetry, fiction, commentaries, interviews, and a virtual gallery. Old and rare books will be available in e-book format, and the page includes a comment/suggestion feature for users to provide feedback. bdnews24.com's editor-in-chief Toufique Imrose Khalidi highlighted the versatility of the service's digital medium: "It's your site. You run it, write for it, promote it, protect it and sustain it. Our job will be to facilitate and to help you do what you want to do. Use and exploit bdnews24.com." bdnews24.com's executive director (news and public affairs) Fazal M Kamal and technology editor Abu Saeed Khan were present at the event. bdnews
